against him</a>, and only about 196.8 million voted for. (The reason for th=
is seems to be mostly that, as a private-equity boss,=C2=A0he is on too man=
y=C2=A0<em>other=C2=A0</em>boards, which corporate governance advocates=C2=
=A0and proxy advisers don=E2=80=99t like.)=C2=A0So he duly resigned from th=
e board. But actually kicking him off the board would be tough, because:</p=
><ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;=
