Just buying a lot of stock will make the stock go up, but buying a lot=C2=
=A0stock is not a crime. Buying a lot of stock and saying =E2=80=9Clol I am=
 pounding this stock to make it go up=E2=80=9D: crime.</p><p style=3D"margi=
n: 16px 0;">Environmental, social and governance investing is a big busines=
s, but it is a relatively=C2=A0<em>new=C2=A0</em>big business, and we are i=
n the early stages of ESG <em>enforcement</em>, of=C2=A0regulators and pros=
ecutors going after financial institutions for misrepresenting their ESG in=
vestment processes. But I suspect it is going to end up looking a lot like =
market manipulation: =E2=80=9CGreenwashing=E2=80=9D will mean (1) making am=
biguously ESG investment choices (buying fossil-fuel companies, etc.) in ES=
G funds and (2) sending emails saying things like =E2=80=9Cthis company is =
bad for ESG but we are buying it anyway.=E2=80=9D ESG is a subjective and c=
omplex enough concept that you can make the case that pretty much any inves=
tment=C2=A0<em>is=C2=A0</em>ESG, or=C2=A0<em>is not=C2=A0</em>ESG; what mak=
es something =E2=80=9Cgreenwashing=E2=80=9D is evidence of=C2=A0<em>intent<=
/em>.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So we <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bl=
oombergbusiness.com/click/27899761.281614/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvb=
S9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDUtMjMvdGhlLXNlYy1nb2VzLWFmdGVyLWdyZWVud2Fz=
